title: Albert Einstein
text:
Introduction
Portfolio Introduction
This portfolio was created as part of the Data Science minor at Brigham Young University, showcasing my skills and experiences in three key areas: Data Analysis, Machine Learning, and Data Visualization. Its primary purpose is to demonstrate the knowledge I have gained throughout the program and how I have applied it to real-world data challenges.

title: Projects
text:
Projects
Sample Projects Overview

Project 1: Data Visualization and Reporting

Developed interactive dashboards to visualize key business metrics and trends.
Automated data cleaning and integration processes to streamline reporting workflows.
Collaborated with stakeholders to ensure insights were actionable and aligned with business goals.



project 1 name here


Project 2: Predictive Modeling

Built machine learning models to forecast customer demand with improved accuracy.
Integrated predictive insights into decision-making processes, reducing stockouts and excess inventory.
Conducted sensitivity analysis to assess the impact of key variables on predictions.



project 2 name here


Project 3: Time Series Analysis

Analyzed historical sales data to identify seasonal patterns and trends.
Designed and implemented time series forecasting models to predict future sales performance.
Provided actionable recommendations to optimize promotional strategies and inventory planning.
